description:
&lt;p&gt;Lancashire teaching hospitals are delighted to offer this exciting opportunity for a registered staff nurse to join our Ophthalmology team. We are looking to recruit nurses who have an interest in the care and experience of patients attending for ophthalmology surgery and outpatient visits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Experience in an Ophthalmic Unit is desirable. You must be motivated, enthusiastic, committed to delivering high standards of patient care with excellent communication skills. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will work across the ophthalmic unit, covering three outpatient clinics and a day ward. The hours of work will be flexible between 07.00 – 19.30, Monday – Friday and 0830-1630 on Saturday. The post will initially be based at Preston but there will be an expectation to work at Chorley hospital in the near future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview Date: 24th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Janet Hughes, sister ward 1 on 01772 522286&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Richardson, sister ophthalmology outpatients on 01772 523501&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachel Blackwell or Debbie Wood, nurse practitioners on 01772 528419.&lt;/p&gt;
